******************************************************************************

Answer: Word stored in grid
Cell: Single cell that stores a letter
Config: Parameters for a game such as grid size, number of letters, time limit, etc
Direction: Lists the 8 directions an answer can point in
Game: Stores the grid, config, sequence for controlling randomness, dictionary of words
Grid: Stores a 2d array of cells, answer map, sequencer, config
Guess: Stores a list of Cell tags that represent a guess
Level: Score, time and stars gained for each level
Position: x and y coordinates that represent a single grid's cell but has no reference to a cell itself
ProgressTracker: Stores levels, scores, config and misc stats such as display and font size 
Selection: Stores a position, direction and length to indicate a guess / answer
Sequencer: Allows a way to randomly traverse grid, directions, letters, etc.
Trie: An efficient dictionary of words
Wordlist: A small wrapper class to create a dictionary

